div.p:
AS to the will of our wiſe God, which is fulfilled in my preſent condition;
I muſt indeed, I am made to acknowledge it; and therefore
for that I have blamed and paſſionately wronged you, I am heartily
ſorry and humbly implore your goodneſſe for to have me excuſed for it;
I ſhall now learn to ſubmit to a divine will, who is juſt in what it doth,
and will juſtifie all thoſe whom it makes uſe of for its accompliſhment, &c.

                  He perſwades her (viz.) Miſtreſs White to ſell a parcell of Plate;
She left the ſale to him, could never have any accompt, only received
eight pounds, p. 67.
